---
alwaysApply: true
---

# Custom cursor rules for Atomic Design UI Component Architecture in Next.js

# General project description
instructions:
  - "This project follows Atomic Design principles for UI component organization."
  - "Components are organized into atoms, molecules, organisms, templates, and pages."
  - "Strict dependency rules between layers must be followed to avoid circular dependencies."

# Folder structure scopes and organization
folders:
  - path: "src/components/atoms/**"
    scope: "Atoms"
    description: "Smallest reusable UI elements, pure presentation-focused."
    import_rules:
      - "Must NOT import molecules, organisms, templates, or pages."
  - path: "src/components/molecules/**"
    scope: "Molecules"
    description: "Groups of atoms, no business logic."
    import_rules:
      - "May ONLY import atoms."
      - "Must NOT import organisms, templates, or pages."
  - path: "src/components/organisms/**"
    scope: "Organisms"
    description: "Complex UI composed of atoms and molecules, business logic allowed."
    import_rules:
      - "May import atoms and molecules."
      - "Must NOT import templates or pages."
  - path: "src/components/templates/**"
    scope: "Templates"
    description: "Page-level layouts, no business logic."
    import_rules:
      - "May import atoms, molecules, and organisms."
  - path: "src/app/**"
    scope: "Pages"
    description: "Route-level implementations inside Next.js app dir."
    import_rules:
      - "May import from any UI layer."

# Composition and design rules
rules:
  - "Atoms must be generic, reusable, and purely presentational with no business logic."
  - "Molecules must also be free of business logic."
  - "Organisms and pages contain feature-specific UI behavior and business logic."
  - "Favor composition over inheritance for building components."
  - "Extract common UI patterns into reusable atoms or molecules."
  - "Use lowercase dashed folder names for all components."

# Additional instructions
additional:
  - "Enforce dependency rules programmatically via lint or build step if possible."
  - "Avoid circular dependencies between component layers."
